01:44.016 --> 01:46.889
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:20.183 --> 02:21.184
-HEY, PAL.

02:24.274 --> 02:26.189
-HOW CAN YOU
MAKE ME GO TO SCHOOL?

02:26.320 --> 02:27.538
LOOK AT THOSE SETS.

02:28.365 --> 02:30.585
-I KNOW IT'S CRUEL
AND UNUSUAL PUNISHMENT.

02:31.325 --> 02:33.065
-WHAT ARE YOU WRITING?
-SHOPPING LIST.

02:33.805 --> 02:35.764
WHAT DO YOU WANT FOR DINNER?
-UH, HOT DOGS.

02:35.894 --> 02:39.333
-OH, COME ON.
I WAS THINKING ABOUT MY
FAMOUS SEAFOOD GUMBO.

02:39.463 --> 02:42.074
-YUCK! TALK ABOUT
CRUEL AND UNUSUAL PUNISHMENT.

02:42.205 --> 02:44.990
-YOU KNOW, I HAVE HAD IT
WITH YOUR JOKES ABOUT
MY COOKING.

02:45.121 --> 02:46.775
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
PUT UP OR SHUT UP?

02:46.905 --> 02:48.429
-FINE, I'LL MAKE
DINNER TONIGHT.

02:49.038 --> 02:53.216
-I'M TALKING ABOUT
A HEALTHY, BALANCED,
EDIBLE MEAL.

02:53.347 --> 02:55.566
-NO HOT DOGS.
NO FROZEN PIZZAS.

02:55.697 --> 02:57.046
-NO PROBLEM.

02:57.177 --> 02:58.874
I'VE BEEN TAKING
A COOKING CLASS AT SCHOOL.

02:59.004 --> 03:00.919
I GET EXTRA CREDIT
FOR EVERYTHING I MAKE
AT HOME.

03:01.050 --> 03:02.573
WHAT TIME DO YOU
WANNA EAT?

03:03.922 --> 03:06.142
-6:30.
-6:30 IT IS.

03:06.273 --> 03:08.188
SEE YA THEN.
-OKAY, PAL.

03:09.667 --> 03:11.016
DON'T STUDY TOO HARD.

03:11.147 --> 03:12.496
-I WON'T.

03:12.627 --> 03:13.758
-LOVE YA.

03:23.942 --> 03:26.902
SWIMMER, YOU ARE
IN A SURFER AREA.
PLEASE MOVE SOUTH.

03:29.948 --> 03:32.124
SWIMMER, YOU'RE
IN A SURFER AREA.

03:32.255 --> 03:34.649
PLEASE MOVE SOUTH
TOWARDS THE PIER.

03:38.522 --> 03:39.480
WHAT?

03:43.092 --> 03:44.311
[SIGHS]

03:56.714 --> 03:58.194
-[SCREAMS]

03:59.326 --> 04:00.631
-DAMN IT.

04:03.243 --> 04:04.809
-[CHATTERING]

04:20.084 --> 04:21.522
-HERE, TAKE THE CAN.

04:21.652 --> 04:23.088
-THANKS.
-HOLD ON.

04:30.835 --> 04:32.489
YOU OKAY?

04:32.620 --> 04:34.056
YOU TOOK A PRETTY GOOD
SHOT FROM THAT BOARD OUT THERE.

04:34.186 --> 04:36.319
-EH, IT WASN'T THAT BAD.

04:36.450 --> 04:38.974
I THINK IT SCARED ME
MORE THAN IT
ACTUALLY HURT.

04:40.018 --> 04:41.455
-DO ME A FAVOR.
TRY MOVING YOUR NECK.

04:44.327 --> 04:45.502
ANY PAIN?

04:45.633 --> 04:47.156
-OH!

04:47.678 --> 04:48.853
ACTUALLY, YEAH.

04:49.376 --> 04:50.290
WOW.

04:51.291 --> 04:53.510
-IF YOU WANT,
I GOT A COLD PACK
IN THE TOWER.

04:53.641 --> 04:55.773
IT WILL HELP PREVENT
SOME OF THE SWELLING

04:55.904 --> 04:56.818
AND CURE THE PAIN.

04:57.471 --> 04:59.081
-YEAH, THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

04:59.211 --> 05:01.431
-OKAY.
-YEAH, GOD, I'M SORRY.

05:01.562 --> 05:03.215
-IT'S OKAY.
COME ON.

05:04.216 --> 05:05.305
-MAN.

05:10.614 --> 05:12.007
-HERE.

05:12.137 --> 05:13.965
PUT THIS ON YOUR SHOULDER.

05:14.096 --> 05:15.967
IT'LL HELP THE SWELLING
GO DOWN.
-THANKS.

05:16.098 --> 05:17.229
-LISTEN, I'M SORRY
ABOUT ALL THIS,

05:17.360 --> 05:19.449
BUT DIDN'T YOU
SEE THE SIGNS?

05:19.580 --> 05:20.885
THIS BEACH IS
FOR SURFING ONLY.

05:21.016 --> 05:23.018
-OH!

05:23.148 --> 05:25.934
-NO, I'M SORRY.
I SHOULD HAVE BEEN
MORE CAREFUL.

05:26.064 --> 05:27.501
-THAT'S A REAL
PRETTY ACCENT.

05:27.631 --> 05:28.458
WHERE ARE YOU FROM?

05:29.067 --> 05:30.025
-ITALY.

05:30.721 --> 05:32.244
-ROME?

05:32.375 --> 05:34.203
-NO, I LIVE IN A SMALL TOWN
OUTSIDE OF NAPLES.

05:35.030 --> 05:36.205
-YOU'RE ON VACATION?

05:37.032 --> 05:38.512
-NO, I'M AN ACTRESS.

05:39.556 --> 05:41.297
-OH.
-I'M HERE WORKING
ON A FILM.

05:42.037 --> 05:44.692
MY NAME'S LENA.
-HI, LENA. I'M MITCH.

05:44.822 --> 05:45.649
I'M FROM VENICE.

05:47.738 --> 05:48.870
VENICE, CALIFORNIA.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.915
-OH, THE OTHER VENICE.

05:51.046 --> 05:52.352
-[BOTH LAUGHING]

06:03.841 --> 06:04.799
-HEY, GUIDO.

06:05.626 --> 06:06.583
WHAT'S WRONG?

06:08.019 --> 06:09.456
WHO'S THE LETTER FROM?

06:09.586 --> 06:12.154
-MAMA.
-IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

06:12.284 --> 06:14.548
-NO, EVERYTHING
IS NOT ALL RIGHT.

06:14.678 --> 06:16.724
-MAMA'S COMING
FOR A VISIT.

06:17.812 --> 06:18.987
-WELL, WHY IS THAT
SO BAD?

06:19.117 --> 06:20.684
-BECAUSE,
WHEN SHE GETS HERE,

06:20.815 --> 06:22.338
SHE'S GOING TO DISCOVER
THAT I'M...

06:22.947 --> 06:23.774
NOT A LIFEGUARD.

06:24.906 --> 06:26.429
-YOU TOLD HER
YOU WERE A LIFEGUARD?

06:28.300 --> 06:29.606
-GUIDO,
HOW COULD YOU DO THAT?

06:30.259 --> 06:32.087
-WELL, WHEN I LEFT MY HOME,

06:32.217 --> 06:34.829
I PROMISED MAMA I WOULD
BECOME SOMEONE SHE WOULD
BE PROUD OF.

06:34.959 --> 06:36.178
THAT'S THE ONLY TIME
I EVER LIED TO HER.

06:37.875 --> 06:39.703
WHO KNEW THIS WAS
GOING TO HAPPEN?

06:39.834 --> 06:41.836
-WELL, DID YOU THINK
YOU WERE GONNA
GET AWAY WITH IT?

06:41.966 --> 06:44.578
-WELL, BECAUSE MAMA
SPENT HER ENTIRE LIFE
IN THE OLD COUNTRY.

06:44.708 --> 06:46.275
SHE NEVER EVEN
LEFT HER VILLAGE.

06:46.406 --> 06:48.059
WHO KNEW ONE MORNING
SHE WOULD WAKE UP

06:48.190 --> 06:50.148
AND DECIDE TO COME
TO AMERICA?

06:50.279 --> 06:51.541
-WELL, I'M SURE IF YOU
TELL HER THE TRUTH,
SHE'LL UNDERSTAND.

06:51.672 --> 06:53.413
-OH, YOU DON'T
KNOW MAMA.

06:53.543 --> 06:55.371
TELLING HER THE TRUTH

06:55.502 --> 06:58.505
WOULD BE LIKE TAKING
A DAGGER AND PLUNGING IT
INTO HER HEART.

07:00.202 --> 07:02.030
-EVERYTHING WILL BE OKAY.

07:14.869 --> 07:17.262
-MITCH'S VOICE:
YOU KNOW, GARNER, I'VE MET
A MILLION GIRLS ON THIS BEACH.

07:18.829 --> 07:20.309
MORE THAN I CAN REMEMBER.

07:22.006 --> 07:23.486
IT'S JUST THAT,
NOW, I'M...

07:23.617 --> 07:25.749
-STARTING TO COME UP
EMPTY FOR YOU?

07:25.880 --> 07:27.751
-YEAH, YEAH.
I'M JUST TIRED OF DOING

07:27.882 --> 07:29.405
THE SAME OLD THING, YOU KNOW?

07:29.536 --> 07:30.885
HOBIE NEEDS
BROTHERS AND SISTERS.

07:31.015 --> 07:33.365
IT'S NO FUN
GROWING UP AN ONLY CHILD.

07:33.496 --> 07:34.758
-YEAH, I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

07:34.889 --> 07:36.891
I COME FROM
A BIG FAMILY MYSELF.

07:38.893 --> 07:40.634
YOU KNOW WHAT
I REMEMBER MOST?

07:41.765 --> 07:42.940
-WHAT'S THAT?

07:44.115 --> 07:45.769
-WAITING TO USE
THE BATHROOM.

07:45.900 --> 07:48.598
-[LAUGHS]

07:48.729 --> 07:51.819
AH, SERIOUSLY, I THINK
MY PRIORITIES HAVE CHANGED,
YOU KNOW?

07:51.949 --> 07:54.778
I MEAN, IT'S NOT
A PHYSICAL THING ANYMORE
WITH THE GIRL.

07:54.909 --> 07:56.606
I'M KINDA
LEANING TOWARDS...

07:57.607 --> 07:59.740
I DON'T KNOW.
I'M LEANING TOWARDS
SETTLING DOWN.

07:59.870 --> 08:01.132
-IT'S CALLED
GETTING OLD, MITCH.

08:01.263 --> 08:03.265
I FEEL THE SAME WAY.

08:03.395 --> 08:05.963
I'D SETTLE DOWN
IN A MINUTE IF I COULD
CONNECT WITH THE RIGHT WOMAN.

08:41.650 --> 08:42.826
-HI.

08:42.957 --> 08:44.741
-HI.
-HOW'S THE SHOULDER?

08:44.872 --> 08:46.047
-OH, MUCH BETTER.
THANK YOU.

08:46.177 --> 08:48.310
-GOOD.
I'VE GOT AN INCIDENT REPORT

08:48.440 --> 08:50.834
I'VE GOTTA FILL OUT HERE.
DO YOU MIND IF I ASK YOU
A COUPLE OF QUESTIONS?

08:50.965 --> 08:52.749
-OH, NO, NO.
NOT AT ALL.
-OKAY.

08:54.969 --> 08:56.231
OKAY.

08:56.361 --> 08:58.668
SO, I KNOW YOUR FIRST NAME
IS LENA.

08:59.321 --> 09:00.278
WHAT'S YOUR LAST NAME?

09:00.409 --> 09:03.543
FIORI.
F-I-O-R-I.

09:03.673 --> 09:05.283
-FIORI.
WHAT'S YOUR ADDRESS?

09:05.414 --> 09:07.242
-2000 MALIBU ROAD.

09:07.372 --> 09:09.461
-WELL, THAT'S A NICE
PART OF TOWN.

09:09.592 --> 09:12.247
-I KNOW. UNFORTUNATELY,
IT'S ONLY A TEMPORARY ADDRESS.

09:12.377 --> 09:13.596
I'M RENTING
FOR THE MONTH.

09:14.379 --> 09:15.424
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN
MY FANTASY

09:15.555 --> 09:18.645
TO ACT
IN A HOLLYWOOD MOVIE,

09:18.775 --> 09:20.647
LIVE IN A MALIBU BEACH HOUSE,

09:20.777 --> 09:23.258
DRIVE A BRAND NEW CORVETTE.

09:23.388 --> 09:24.912
YOU KNOW, JUST LIKE
ANNETTE FUNICELLO.

09:27.305 --> 09:30.047
AND NOW, I'VE EVEN BEEN
RESCUED BY A HANDSOME
LIFEGUARD.

09:30.178 --> 09:33.094
-WELL, SOUNDS LIKE YOU
ARE ON A ROLL.

09:33.224 --> 09:34.399
-YEAH.

09:36.663 --> 09:37.751
-'KAY.

09:40.580 --> 09:41.537
-ANY OTHER QUESTIONS?

09:42.190 --> 09:43.887
-UH, YEAH.
ONE LAST QUESTION,

09:44.018 --> 09:45.236
RIGHT HERE.
UM...

09:46.020 --> 09:47.978
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO HAVE DINNER WITH ME?

09:48.109 --> 09:50.067
-[LAUGHS]

09:52.504 --> 09:54.289
THAT'S A VERY TEMPTING OFFER.

09:57.031 --> 09:58.641
[STAMMERS]
BUT I--

09:58.772 --> 10:00.643
I'M ON A VERY TIGHT SCHEDULE.

10:00.774 --> 10:02.732
IT'S TRUE.
I SHOULD BE HOME RIGHT NOW
LEARNING MY LINES.

10:03.428 --> 10:04.516
-EXCUSE ME.

10:05.605 --> 10:07.084
WAS THAT A YES
OR A NO?

10:08.695 --> 10:09.521
-THAT WAS A MAYBE.

10:09.652 --> 10:11.523
-A MAYBE?

10:11.654 --> 10:12.612
A DEFINITE MAYBE?

10:14.048 --> 10:15.310
-MAYBE.

10:16.006 --> 10:16.964
-AH-HA.

10:17.965 --> 10:20.054
AH...

10:20.184 --> 10:22.578
-I KNOW, I KNOW, I KNOW.
IT'S A TERRIBLE HABIT.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.319
I AM TRYING
TO QUIT.

10:25.537 --> 10:28.671
LOOK, PEOPLE IN EUROPE
JUST AREN'T AS
HEALTH CONSCIOUS

10:28.802 --> 10:30.281
AS YOU AMERICANS.

10:30.412 --> 10:31.979
OH, I'M NOT
A VEGETARIAN EITHER.

10:32.109 --> 10:34.155
-NEITHER AM I.
DO WE HAVE A DATE?

10:36.331 --> 10:37.941
-MAYBE.

10:39.203 --> 10:40.552
-WHOA-HO.

10:40.683 --> 10:41.771
-CIAO.

10:45.079 --> 10:46.341
-HEY, PAL.

10:46.471 --> 10:48.386
-HEY, LOOKS LIKE
YOU MADE A NEW FRIEND.

10:48.517 --> 10:49.823
-MAYBE.

10:49.953 --> 10:52.086
-MAYBE?

10:52.216 --> 10:53.391
-ARE YOU SAYING THAT
OLD BUCHANNON CHARM
IS STARTING TO WEAR THIN?

10:53.522 --> 10:55.045
-I DON'T KNOW, PAL.

10:55.176 --> 10:56.307
SHE'S A DOLL, HUH?

11:20.767 --> 11:22.725
-MAN:
DUDE, NICE CAR.

11:22.856 --> 11:24.292
-MAN #2:
PROBABLY HAS MONEY.

11:29.776 --> 11:31.908
-MAN #1:
LET'S FOLLOW HER HOME
AND FIND OUT.

12:25.657 --> 12:27.747
MALIBU COLONY,
LOOKING GOOD.

12:46.809 --> 12:48.985
DON'T SAY A WORD, SWEETIE.
GIVE ME THE KEYS.

12:50.857 --> 12:52.772
-[MUFFLED SHOUTING]

12:54.599 --> 12:56.993
-HURRY UP.
-LET'S GO.

12:57.124 --> 12:58.995
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

13:02.869 --> 13:04.653
-GUIDO: YEAH, BUT SEE,
SHE'S VERY SENSITIVE.

13:04.784 --> 13:07.264
AND AT THIS TIME IN HER LIFE,
SOMETHING LIKE THIS COULD BE--

13:07.395 --> 13:09.527
-GUIDO, I WISH WE COULD
HELP YOU OUT, I REALLY DO,

13:09.658 --> 13:11.791
BUT IF MITCH OR STEPHANIE
WERE TO FIND OUT

13:11.921 --> 13:13.705
WE LET YOU PRETEND
TO BE A LIFEGUARD,

13:13.836 --> 13:15.882
WE COULD GET SUSPENDED.
-NO, WE COULD GET FIRED.

13:16.012 --> 13:17.927
-YEAH, I UNDERSTAND
AND EVERYTHING.

13:18.058 --> 13:19.842
BUT LOOK, LOOK.

13:19.973 --> 13:22.062
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
I'LL JUST BREAK IT
TO HER GENTLY,

13:22.192 --> 13:24.629
AND THEN, HOPE THAT IT'S
NOT TOO MUCH OF A SHOCK.

13:24.760 --> 13:26.675
-WHEN'S SHE COMING?
-HUH?

13:26.806 --> 13:29.896
OH, HER BOAT, IT ARRIVES
EARLY TOMORROW MORNING
AT THE DOCKS.

13:31.114 --> 13:32.681
-SHE'S COMING
ON A BOAT.

13:32.812 --> 13:34.465
-WOMAN: OH, MI SCUSI,
COULD YOU TELL ME, PLEASE,

13:34.596 --> 13:36.816
WHERE I COULD FIND
GUIDO TORZINI?

13:38.600 --> 13:39.688
-MAMA.

13:39.819 --> 13:42.125
-GUIDO.
-MAMA.

13:42.256 --> 13:43.431
-GUIDO.

13:43.561 --> 13:44.780
-MAMA.

13:44.911 --> 13:46.826
-[CRYING]
GUIDO.

13:46.956 --> 13:49.437
OH, GUIDO.

13:49.567 --> 13:52.614
OH, LET ME LOOK AT YOU.

13:52.744 --> 13:55.617
MY SON, THE LIFEGUARD.

13:56.270 --> 13:58.228
-I THOUGHT YOU WERE
COMING IN EARLY
TOMORROW MORNING?

13:58.359 --> 14:00.230
-OH, THAT WAS ON
THE FISHING TRAWLER.

14:00.361 --> 14:02.580
I TOOK A FREIGHTER INSTEAD.

14:02.711 --> 14:04.844
OH, GUIDO.

14:04.974 --> 14:07.716
YOU MAKE YOUR MAMA'S
DREAMS COME TRUE.

14:07.847 --> 14:10.197
IF ONLY YOUR PAPA
COULD SEE YOU.

14:10.327 --> 14:13.069
GOD REST HIS SOUL.
HE'D BE SO PROUD.

14:13.200 --> 14:15.158
-OH, MAMA DON'T CRY.

14:15.289 --> 14:17.247
-[CRYING]
-COME ON, MAMA. PLEASE.

14:17.378 --> 14:19.119
DON'T CRY.
CONTROL YOURSELF.

14:19.249 --> 14:20.990
MAMA.

14:21.121 --> 14:22.513
-YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO INTRODUCE ME
TO YOUR FRIENDS?

14:22.644 --> 14:24.298
-HUH?
UM...

14:24.428 --> 14:26.474
MAMA, THIS IS
C.J. AND SUMMER.

14:26.604 --> 14:28.215
C.J. AND SUMMER,
THIS IS MAMA.

14:28.345 --> 14:30.565
-HI, IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU.
-HI.

14:30.695 --> 14:33.394
-[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

14:33.524 --> 14:36.484
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
THEY WERE SO BEAUTIFUL.

14:37.615 --> 14:39.617
-WELL, WE'D BETTER
BE GOING.

14:39.748 --> 14:42.055
BUT DON'T FORGET, YOUR SHIFT
STARTS TOMORROW MORNING
AT 7:00 SHARP.

14:43.534 --> 14:45.493
-YEAH, TOWER 12.

14:47.147 --> 14:50.019
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU,
MRS. TORZINI. BUH-BYE.

14:50.150 --> 14:51.673
-BYE. CIAO.

14:51.803 --> 14:53.457
LIKEWISE.

14:53.588 --> 14:56.069
OH, GUIDO.
-MAMA.

14:56.199 --> 14:58.636
-GUIDO, GUIDO.
-MAMA.

15:00.116 --> 15:02.249
-[WEEPING]

15:07.602 --> 15:09.256
-[MUFFLED]
HELLO?

15:10.257 --> 15:11.432
-FLYING IN. OH!

15:11.562 --> 15:13.173
-THANK YOU.

15:13.303 --> 15:14.783
[SIGHS]

15:14.914 --> 15:16.524
WHAT HAPPENED?

15:16.654 --> 15:18.134
-I'LL CLEAN UP.

15:18.265 --> 15:20.310
-NOT WITHOUT FEDERAL AID.

15:20.441 --> 15:22.922
-DID YOU GET ONIONS?
THE RECIPE CALLS FOR
FINELY CHOPPED-- ONE?

15:23.923 --> 15:25.489
GREAT.
WHAT ABOUT THE PARSLEY?

15:25.620 --> 15:27.056
-IN THE FRIDGE.

15:30.668 --> 15:32.148
-WHAT ARE YOU
MAKING, ANYWAY?

15:32.279 --> 15:34.890
-CHICKEN PARISIENNE,
HOBIE STYLE.

15:35.021 --> 15:36.892
-THIS NUMBER MEAN
ANYTHING TO YOU?

15:37.023 --> 15:38.546
-UH...

15:38.676 --> 15:40.200
GARNER.
THAT'S WHERE HE'S AT.

15:40.330 --> 15:41.244
-HMM.

15:46.989 --> 15:48.599
-ELLERBEE.
-HEY, BUDDY.
WHAT'S UP?

15:49.818 --> 15:53.343
-THAT ACTRESS YOU MET
ON THE BEACH?

15:54.823 --> 15:56.346
WELL, SHE...

15:56.477 --> 15:57.347
RAN INTO A LITTLE TROUBLE.

15:58.044 --> 15:59.567
-WHAT HAPPENED?

16:00.307 --> 16:02.657
-A COUPLE OF GUYS
BROKE INTO HER HOUSE.
LOOKS LIKE A FOLLOW HOME.

16:02.787 --> 16:04.746
I'LL SEE YOU
AT THE STATION.

16:22.546 --> 16:24.461
-HERE YOU GO.

16:24.592 --> 16:25.723
-THANK YOU.

16:25.854 --> 16:27.464
AND THANK YOU
FOR COMING.

16:27.595 --> 16:29.031
-IT'S OKAY.
GARNER SAID
YOU COULD USE A FRIEND.

16:29.162 --> 16:31.251
-I'VE NEVER BEEN
SO FRIGHTENED IN MY LIFE.

16:31.947 --> 16:33.644
I THOUGHT I WAS
GONNA DIE.

16:34.950 --> 16:37.648
LOOK AT MY HANDS.
THEY'RE STILL SHAKING.

16:37.779 --> 16:39.737
-IT'S OKAY.
HEY, HEY.

16:39.868 --> 16:41.261
IT'S OKAY.
YOU'RE SAFE NOW.

16:41.391 --> 16:43.480
